Text.SourceString: Oh! Hi, there…
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! Hi, there…

Text.SourceString: My name is <NPCName>Rafael</>.//<portrait=concerned>Umm…//<portrait=normal>I’m one of the blacksmiths here in Starlet Town.
Text.LocalizedString: My name is <NPCName>Rafael</>.//<portrait=concerned>Umm…//<portrait=normal>I’m one of the blacksmiths here in Starlet Town.

Text.SourceString: We get a lot of work from the town.//You know, like, um, setting up decorations and stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: We get a lot of work from the town.//You know, like, um, setting up decorations and stuff.

Text.SourceString: I don't mind, really...cleaning up the town. It's where I grew up.//This whole town is my playground, and I want to take care of it.//If you, uh, wouldn't mind helping to keep it clean, I'd appreciate it.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't mind, really...cleaning up the town. It's where I grew up.//This whole town is my playground, and I want to take care of it.//If you, uh, wouldn't mind helping to keep it clean, I'd appreciate it.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I should start gardening. I've been relying a bit too much on foraging lately.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I should start gardening. I've been relying a bit too much on foraging lately.

Text.SourceString: It's been just mushrooms for a while, and I'm, uh, getting a bit tired of them... Yuck.
Text.LocalizedString: It's been just mushrooms for a while, and I'm, uh, getting a bit tired of them... Yuck.

Text.SourceString: Our shop hasn't changed since Mom and Dad retired.
Text.LocalizedString: Our shop hasn't changed since Mom and Dad retired.

Text.SourceString: I mean, it's not bad, um, but a little upgrade wouldn't hurt, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: I mean, it's not bad, um, but a little upgrade wouldn't hurt, you know.

Text.SourceString: I have all these ideas for weapons, but I can’t make them just yet.//<portrait=concerned>Our current furnace isn’t up to it.
Text.LocalizedString: I have all these ideas for weapons, but I can’t make them just yet.//<portrait=concerned>Our current furnace isn’t up to it.

Text.SourceString: Once we upgrade the furnace, hopefully, we can make more advanced weapons and tools.
Text.LocalizedString: Once we upgrade the furnace, hopefully, we can make more advanced weapons and tools.

Text.SourceString: Uhh... Something wrong?
Text.LocalizedString: Uhh... Something wrong?

Text.SourceString: Umm… After work, I usually just cook dinner or something. I don’t know…//<portrait=sad>Did that answer your question?
Text.LocalizedString: Umm… After work, I usually just cook dinner or something. I don’t know…//<portrait=sad>Did that answer your question?

Text.SourceString: I don't really hang out at the Tavern much.//Sometimes, I go to the lake if I need to unwind.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't really hang out at the Tavern much.//Sometimes, I go to the lake if I need to unwind.

Text.SourceString: My brother and I can upgrade all kinds of tools.//You just need to bring us the ore.
Text.LocalizedString: My brother and I can upgrade all kinds of tools.//You just need to bring us the ore.

Text.SourceString: And some compensation for our labor would be nice.
Text.LocalizedString: And some compensation for our labor would be nice.

Text.SourceString: We only accept money as payment. Sorry.
Text.LocalizedString: We only accept money as payment. Sorry.

Text.SourceString: The cemetery is so quiet. And the lake too.//It’s a great place to read horror novels.
Text.LocalizedString: The cemetery is so quiet. And the lake too.//It’s a great place to read horror novels.

Text.SourceString: Yes, um, I do read other books too.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes, um, I do read other books too.

Text.SourceString: I like peace and quiet.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, you too? Well, we’re kind of the same, then. Is that why you moved onto your grandparents’ farm?
Text.LocalizedString: I like peace and quiet.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, you too? Well, we’re kind of the same, then. Is that why you moved onto your grandparents’ farm?

Text.SourceString: I get it, though. It’s hard to get peace and quiet when you work next to a massive furnace all day.
Text.LocalizedString: I get it, though. It’s hard to get peace and quiet when you work next to a massive furnace all day.

Text.SourceString: Favorite sushi? Umm… I like all sushi I guess.//So, um, as long as it’s fresh, any kind is fine by me.
Text.LocalizedString: Favorite sushi? Umm… I like all sushi I guess.//So, um, as long as it’s fresh, any kind is fine by me.

Text.SourceString: You fish a lot, don’t you? You must eat a lot of fish.
Text.LocalizedString: You fish a lot, don’t you? You must eat a lot of fish.

Text.SourceString: We get our ore from the cavern. The one north of the forest.//If you don’t see the ore you need, um, maybe keep digging?
Text.LocalizedString: We get our ore from the cavern. The one north of the forest.//If you don’t see the ore you need, um, maybe keep digging?

Text.SourceString: When you upgrade your tools, they’ll change color a bit.//It depends on the material.
Text.LocalizedString: When you upgrade your tools, they’ll change color a bit.//It depends on the material.

Text.SourceString: Don’t be worried. It’s normal.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t be worried. It’s normal.

Text.SourceString: There’s nothing I like more than a good horror movie.//It keeps you on the edge of your seat.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s nothing I like more than a good horror movie.//It keeps you on the edge of your seat.

Text.SourceString: Okay, maybe trying out a new weapon.//<portrait=happy>That can get the heart beating, too.
Text.LocalizedString: Okay, maybe trying out a new weapon.//<portrait=happy>That can get the heart beating, too.

Text.SourceString: Oh no, I haven’t had time to visit the cemetery.//<portrait=normal>Maybe next Monday.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no, I haven’t had time to visit the cemetery.//<portrait=normal>Maybe next Monday.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Pablo</> spends a lot of time in the garage. He seems to <Italic>always</> be calibrating his TV.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Pablo</> spends a lot of time in the garage. He seems to <Italic>always</> be calibrating his TV.

Text.SourceString: Having a big empty place in the middle of nowhere sounds great, to be honest.
Text.LocalizedString: Having a big empty place in the middle of nowhere sounds great, to be honest.

Text.SourceString: I still have work to do, so I can’t go to the inn today.//I usually visit my niece there on Sundays. Get to see the twins, too.
Text.LocalizedString: I still have work to do, so I can’t go to the inn today.//I usually visit my niece there on Sundays. Get to see the twins, too.

Text.SourceString: The air is different at the beach. It’s saltier.//<portrait=annoyed>And a bit sticky.
Text.LocalizedString: The air is different at the beach. It’s saltier.//<portrait=annoyed>And a bit sticky.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I could live there full time and walk to work.//<portrait=surprised>But it would be a waste of money.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I could live there full time and walk to work.//<portrait=surprised>But it would be a waste of money.

Text.SourceString: We’re closed today. The store also closes early on Saturdays.//It's our family day.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re closed today. The store also closes early on Saturdays.//It's our family day.

Text.SourceString: You can sell metal bars, and they go for more than raw ore.
Text.LocalizedString: You can sell metal bars, and they go for more than raw ore.

Text.SourceString: Business is booming. We need more space.//Or better tools.
Text.LocalizedString: Business is booming. We need more space.//Or better tools.

Text.SourceString: Another customer? Coming out of the woodwork these days, aren’t ya?
Text.LocalizedString: Another customer? Coming out of the woodwork these days, aren’t ya?

Text.SourceString: What can I do for you?
Text.LocalizedString: What can I do for you?

Text.SourceString: I use my forge, my bellows, and my own two hands.//Sometimes, though, I wish I had a little extra help.
Text.LocalizedString: I use my forge, my bellows, and my own two hands.//Sometimes, though, I wish I had a little extra help.

Text.SourceString: Aside from <NPCName>Pablo</>, of course.//He's really, um, great.
Text.LocalizedString: Aside from <NPCName>Pablo</>, of course.//He's really, um, great.

Text.SourceString: My work keeps me so busy. I sometimes wish...
Text.LocalizedString: My work keeps me so busy. I sometimes wish...

Text.SourceString: No. No more, um, wishing. Want something? You work for it.
Text.LocalizedString: No. No more, um, wishing. Want something? You work for it.

Text.SourceString: Have you heard the legends about magic on this island?//<portrait=annoyed>Bunch of silly hand-waving and mumbling, if you ask me.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you heard the legends about magic on this island?//<portrait=annoyed>Bunch of silly hand-waving and mumbling, if you ask me.

Text.SourceString: Hopefully, I’m wrong… ’Cause that would be really cool.
Text.LocalizedString: Hopefully, I’m wrong… ’Cause that would be really cool.

Text.SourceString: I love creating weapons. One day, I hope to make something truly special.//Something that, um, people will remember me for.
Text.LocalizedString: I love creating weapons. One day, I hope to make something truly special.//Something that, um, people will remember me for.

Text.SourceString: There’s more ore than what you find down in the cavern. Some impressive stuff.//Some might call it, um, mythical…//<portrait=annoyed>Most of it probably just old tales, though.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s more ore than what you find down in the cavern. Some impressive stuff.//Some might call it, um, mythical…//<portrait=annoyed>Most of it probably just old tales, though.

Text.SourceString: But tales start somewhere, right? There could be a sliver of truth in ’em.
Text.LocalizedString: But tales start somewhere, right? There could be a sliver of truth in ’em.

Text.SourceString: I tried carpentry, but it’s not for me.//I can handle small things or maybe fix a cabinet, but a whole house is too much.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried carpentry, but it’s not for me.//I can handle small things or maybe fix a cabinet, but a whole house is too much.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Joko</> and <NPCName>Dinda</> are top-notch carpenters, anyway.//I don’t think the market here is big enough for another carpenter, even if I wanted to be one.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Joko</> and <NPCName>Dinda</> are top-notch carpenters, anyway.//I don’t think the market here is big enough for another carpenter, even if I wanted to be one.

Text.SourceString: I like making weapons more than upgrading tools.//<portrait=happy>We don't have a lot of resources for making weapons, but that's not gonna, um, stop me.
Text.LocalizedString: I like making weapons more than upgrading tools.//<portrait=happy>We don't have a lot of resources for making weapons, but that's not gonna, um, stop me.

Text.SourceString: There are some weapons I made that I can't sell, they didn't pass the safety test.//<portrait=happy>Maybe, um, I could show them to you sometime.
Text.LocalizedString: There are some weapons I made that I can't sell, they didn't pass the safety test.//<portrait=happy>Maybe, um, I could show them to you sometime.

Text.SourceString: Hillside is a nice place to live. Just far enough from the town.//The woodland, though…it's a bit too close to everyone for me.//<portrait=annoyed>Whatever, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Hillside is a nice place to live. Just far enough from the town.//The woodland, though…it's a bit too close to everyone for me.//<portrait=annoyed>Whatever, though.

Text.SourceString: Argh.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, hey! Didn’t see you there.
Text.LocalizedString: Argh.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, hey! Didn’t see you there.

Text.SourceString: You can check out our shop if you need some new weapons. I make most of them myself.
Text.LocalizedString: You can check out our shop if you need some new weapons. I make most of them myself.

Text.SourceString: And sometimes <NPCName>Pablo</> helps out too.
Text.LocalizedString: And sometimes <NPCName>Pablo</> helps out too.

Text.SourceString: We're open pretty much every day, but the store closes early tomorrow.//<portrait=happy>And we’re closed on Sundays.
Text.LocalizedString: We're open pretty much every day, but the store closes early tomorrow.//<portrait=happy>And we’re closed on Sundays.

Text.SourceString: If we didn't stick to a schedule, we'd end up working all the time. That's not, um, healthy…
Text.LocalizedString: If we didn't stick to a schedule, we'd end up working all the time. That's not, um, healthy…

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina</> is a great kid. I feel like <NPCName>Antonio</> is a bit too hard on her sometimes.//But I’m not a parent, so…
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina</> is a great kid. I feel like <NPCName>Antonio</> is a bit too hard on her sometimes.//But I’m not a parent, so…

Text.SourceString: She’s the daughter of my cousin, <NPCName>Antonio</>.//Yeah, she calls me and <NPCName>Pablo</> uncle, even though we’re not her dad’s actual brothers. It’s kind of a thing in our family… I don’t know.//It’s not weird for me…
Text.LocalizedString: She’s the daughter of my cousin, <NPCName>Antonio</>.//Yeah, she calls me and <NPCName>Pablo</> uncle, even though we’re not her dad’s actual brothers. It’s kind of a thing in our family… I don’t know.//It’s not weird for me…

Text.SourceString: Legend has it you can make some really incredible stuff with the right ore.
Text.LocalizedString: Legend has it you can make some really incredible stuff with the right ore.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever heard of the Ironeye Hammer? Legend says it’s a magic hammer that forges things by itself!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever heard of the Ironeye Hammer? Legend says it’s a magic hammer that forges things by itself!

Text.SourceString: I don't really, um, believe it. But just think about the time I'd save if it were true…
Text.LocalizedString: I don't really, um, believe it. But just think about the time I'd save if it were true…

Text.SourceString: According to the legend, the Ironeye Hammer even talks to you while it works!//<portrait=happy>I wonder if it knows any, um, jokes.
Text.LocalizedString: According to the legend, the Ironeye Hammer even talks to you while it works!//<portrait=happy>I wonder if it knows any, um, jokes.

Text.SourceString: I’d be a fool to put my trust in the Ironeye Hammer.//It works by itself, but the legends don’t say whether it’s a good worker.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d be a fool to put my trust in the Ironeye Hammer.//It works by itself, but the legends don’t say whether it’s a good worker.

Text.SourceString: Does it get tired? Does it take personal days?//<portrait=surprised>The legends are mysteriously silent on these issues.
Text.LocalizedString: Does it get tired? Does it take personal days?//<portrait=surprised>The legends are mysteriously silent on these issues.

Text.SourceString: It’s been a couple days since my explorer friend left to find tevandium. I can’t wait until he comes back!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s been a couple days since my explorer friend left to find tevandium. I can’t wait until he comes back!

Text.SourceString: Do you think the explorer found the tevandium yet?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think the explorer found the tevandium yet?

Text.SourceString: I wonder if it’s real. Tevandium, I mean.//The explorer said he’d seen it, but if it’s mythical, who knows what he really saw?
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if it’s real. Tevandium, I mean.//The explorer said he’d seen it, but if it’s mythical, who knows what he really saw?

Text.SourceString: I hope it’s real. I have big plans.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it’s real. I have big plans.

Text.SourceString: I would have expected the explorer to be back with the tevandium by now. I hope he’s okay.
Text.LocalizedString: I would have expected the explorer to be back with the tevandium by now. I hope he’s okay.

Text.SourceString: The Ironeye Hammer isn’t the only tool you can make with tevandium. Just the most famous.//<portrait=happy>I can’t help but let my mind wander.
Text.LocalizedString: The Ironeye Hammer isn’t the only tool you can make with tevandium. Just the most famous.//<portrait=happy>I can’t help but let my mind wander.

Text.SourceString: The Greatstone Amulet, the Firestarter’s Axe… This could change the entire shop.//<portrait=happy>The entire island!
Text.LocalizedString: The Greatstone Amulet, the Firestarter’s Axe… This could change the entire shop.//<portrait=happy>The entire island!

Text.SourceString: What if the explorer decided to keep all the tevandium for himself?//I just realized he never told me where the cave was, exactly…
Text.LocalizedString: What if the explorer decided to keep all the tevandium for himself?//I just realized he never told me where the cave was, exactly…

Text.SourceString: Maybe I shouldn’t have paid half up front.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I shouldn’t have paid half up front.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Pablo</> is my older brother.//We look a bit alike, right?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Pablo</> is my older brother.//We look a bit alike, right?

Text.SourceString: We don't have any other siblings...just us two.
Text.LocalizedString: We don't have any other siblings...just us two.

Text.SourceString: I smelt ore all day sometimes. *sighs* So, please don’t mind my dirty clothes.
Text.LocalizedString: I smelt ore all day sometimes. *sighs* So, please don’t mind my dirty clothes.

Text.SourceString: It's easy to lose track of time. Smelting ore is such a, um...mundane job.//My body kind of goes into autopilot.
Text.LocalizedString: It's easy to lose track of time. Smelting ore is such a, um...mundane job.//My body kind of goes into autopilot.

Text.SourceString: You know, my parents used to be farmers, like you. They said you gotta be strong to do it.//Kudos to you.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, my parents used to be farmers, like you. They said you gotta be strong to do it.//Kudos to you.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, sure, I could see myself as a farmer.//Didn't we talk about this already?
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, sure, I could see myself as a farmer.//Didn't we talk about this already?

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe people throw out perfectly good food around here.//What a waste.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe people throw out perfectly good food around here.//What a waste.

Text.SourceString: I’m visiting my niece tomorrow. It’s a good time to go to the beach, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m visiting my niece tomorrow. It’s a good time to go to the beach, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: I also help out at the inn, doing odd jobs. Changing light bulbs and all that.//The twins never asked me to do anything… They don't really need my help, but I don't mind.
Text.LocalizedString: I also help out at the inn, doing odd jobs. Changing light bulbs and all that.//The twins never asked me to do anything… They don't really need my help, but I don't mind.

Text.SourceString: Lately, I feel like I'm not all there. Need to snap out of it.
Text.LocalizedString: Lately, I feel like I'm not all there. Need to snap out of it.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I need a vacation. Get away from the forge for a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I need a vacation. Get away from the forge for a bit.

Text.SourceString: I know what happened, <PlayerName>$player</>. I figured it out. I sent that explorer to his doom!
Text.LocalizedString: I know what happened, <PlayerName>$player</>. I figured it out. I sent that explorer to his doom!

Text.SourceString: That’s the only explanation for why he hasn’t come back. What a fool I’ve been!
Text.LocalizedString: That’s the only explanation for why he hasn’t come back. What a fool I’ve been!

Text.SourceString: You want something done, do it yourself.//I should have just paid him to tell me the location of the ore, instead of making him get it for me.
Text.LocalizedString: You want something done, do it yourself.//I should have just paid him to tell me the location of the ore, instead of making him get it for me.

Text.SourceString: I’m sure that explorer will be back with my tevandium any day now.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m sure that explorer will be back with my tevandium any day now.

Text.SourceString: Purifying the tevandium will be hard, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m not even sure I can do it. But I have to try!
Text.LocalizedString: Purifying the tevandium will be hard, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’m not even sure I can do it. But I have to try!

Text.SourceString: I’m still having a hard time removing the impurities from the tevandium.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m still having a hard time removing the impurities from the tevandium.

Text.SourceString: If I can’t remove them, I’m wondering if I could just go ahead and make the Ironeye Hammer anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: If I can’t remove them, I’m wondering if I could just go ahead and make the Ironeye Hammer anyway.

Text.SourceString: Summer feels a bit too much for me. I, um, prefer Winter.//<portrait=concerned>Uh…or maybe Fall.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer feels a bit too much for me. I, um, prefer Winter.//<portrait=concerned>Uh…or maybe Fall.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to the hot pot at the Cherry Blossom Festival.//<portrait=annoyed>Not looking forward to fishing the vegetables out of my portion, though…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to the hot pot at the Cherry Blossom Festival.//<portrait=annoyed>Not looking forward to fishing the vegetables out of my portion, though…

Text.SourceString: The cherry blossoms are looking really nice this year.
Text.LocalizedString: The cherry blossoms are looking really nice this year.

Text.SourceString: I'm glad to see the birds out and about, but sometimes I wish they'd quiet down a little. Just a little.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm glad to see the birds out and about, but sometimes I wish they'd quiet down a little. Just a little.

Text.SourceString: Are you busy, <PlayerName>$player</>? I hear farmers are usually really busy in Spring.//Do you need help?//<portrait=concerned>I don’t think I can help, though. I’m a little busy myself. Sorry…
Text.LocalizedString: Are you busy, <PlayerName>$player</>? I hear farmers are usually really busy in Spring.//Do you need help?//<portrait=concerned>I don’t think I can help, though. I’m a little busy myself. Sorry…

Text.SourceString: I wish Winter could be longer, but new horror films are usually released in Fall… So, that’s something to look forward to.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish Winter could be longer, but new horror films are usually released in Fall… So, that’s something to look forward to.

Text.SourceString: I just want to stay outside all day…get some fresh air.
Text.LocalizedString: I just want to stay outside all day…get some fresh air.

Text.SourceString: I rented this horror film yesterday. <Italic>Alakazam</> – a classic, I think. I watch it every Summer.//<portrait=annoyed>Anyway, I haven’t had a chance to watch it. I think I’m gonna need to pay late fees again.*sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: I rented this horror film yesterday. <Italic>Alakazam</> – a classic, I think. I watch it every Summer.//<portrait=annoyed>Anyway, I haven’t had a chance to watch it. I think I’m gonna need to pay late fees again.*sighs*

Text.SourceString: Working in front of the furnace in Summer is…intense. //I can handle it in other seasons, but Summer is just too much.
Text.LocalizedString: Working in front of the furnace in Summer is…intense. //I can handle it in other seasons, but Summer is just too much.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Pablo</> keeps inviting me to the Tavern, but I keep telling him I just want to stay in.//<portrait=happy>I don't like the Tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Pablo</> keeps inviting me to the Tavern, but I keep telling him I just want to stay in.//<portrait=happy>I don't like the Tavern.

Text.SourceString: Sorry I’m such a bummer, <PlayerName>$player</>. I think it’s just the Summer heat… I hope.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry I’m such a bummer, <PlayerName>$player</>. I think it’s just the Summer heat… I hope.

Text.SourceString: How’s your Summer so far? Mine’s okay. I spend a lot of nights watching horror films in my room.//No, no. I don’t have a TV in my room. I have this tablet… Anyway, never mind. It’s small and not very fancy.
Text.LocalizedString: How’s your Summer so far? Mine’s okay. I spend a lot of nights watching horror films in my room.//No, no. I don’t have a TV in my room. I have this tablet… Anyway, never mind. It’s small and not very fancy.

Text.SourceString: I can hear the bugs singing at night outside my window.//Yeah, sure...it’s nice.
Text.LocalizedString: I can hear the bugs singing at night outside my window.//Yeah, sure...it’s nice.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I can get some ceiling fans installed for next Summer.//<portrait=annoyed>All I do is fan myself in bed with old newspapers… Makes me feel like a salmon being smoked.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I can get some ceiling fans installed for next Summer.//<portrait=annoyed>All I do is fan myself in bed with old newspapers… Makes me feel like a salmon being smoked.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Valentina</> can play in the sun the whole day – in this heat.//I don’t know… I don’t think it’s healthy, right?//What do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Valentina</> can play in the sun the whole day – in this heat.//I don’t know… I don’t think it’s healthy, right?//What do you think?

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to <NPCName>Betty’s</> homemade mooncakes. They’re always the highlight of Fall for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to <NPCName>Betty’s</> homemade mooncakes. They’re always the highlight of Fall for me.

Text.SourceString: I wonder what horror films are coming out this Fall.//I like the ones with jump scares. Just nice classic horror films with ghosts.//<portrait=concerned>Um…
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what horror films are coming out this Fall.//I like the ones with jump scares. Just nice classic horror films with ghosts.//<portrait=concerned>Um…

Text.SourceString: Planning to spend the weekend nights watching Fall films with, um, ghosts…//Even better if they're ghosts from folk tales. What are you, um, gonna do?
Text.LocalizedString: Planning to spend the weekend nights watching Fall films with, um, ghosts…//Even better if they're ghosts from folk tales. What are you, um, gonna do?

Text.SourceString: It’s still a bit too warm to spend all day in front of the furnace.//<portrait=normal>But at least the wind feels pretty nice.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s still a bit too warm to spend all day in front of the furnace.//<portrait=normal>But at least the wind feels pretty nice.

Text.SourceString: I wonder what Beluga Bay will be showing at this year’s Harvest Festival…
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what Beluga Bay will be showing at this year’s Harvest Festival…

Text.SourceString: Fall might be my favorite season, I guess.//I’m lucky to live here. It's easy to just go out and enjoy nature whenever I want to.
Text.LocalizedString: Fall might be my favorite season, I guess.//I’m lucky to live here. It's easy to just go out and enjoy nature whenever I want to.

Text.SourceString: Winter is nice… I like it.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter is nice… I like it.

Text.SourceString: I think I have the ingredients to make ramen tonight.//Gonna eat it in my room and watch funny videos on my tablet.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I have the ingredients to make ramen tonight.//Gonna eat it in my room and watch funny videos on my tablet.

Text.SourceString: I forgot to close my bedroom windows the other day before going to work…and my bed froze.//Well, yeah… No, it wasn’t actually frozen. It was just really cold.//<portrait=sad>Um…sorry.
Text.LocalizedString: I forgot to close my bedroom windows the other day before going to work…and my bed froze.//Well, yeah… No, it wasn’t actually frozen. It was just really cold.//<portrait=sad>Um…sorry.

Text.SourceString: If I get too hot, I just step outside and let the Winter air cool me down.//I can do that now…because it’s Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: If I get too hot, I just step outside and let the Winter air cool me down.//I can do that now…because it’s Winter.

Text.SourceString: Are you warm? Make sure to stay warm, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you warm? Make sure to stay warm, okay?

Text.SourceString: This Winter is a little dry.//My hands hurt if I wash them too much. But it’s nothing unbearable. It’s okay…
Text.LocalizedString: This Winter is a little dry.//My hands hurt if I wash them too much. But it’s nothing unbearable. It’s okay…

Text.SourceString: Winter coats are, um, hard to wash. They're very thick. Take ages to dry.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter coats are, um, hard to wash. They're very thick. Take ages to dry.

Text.SourceString: I like the cold wind. It feels good against my face after a whole day in front of the hot furnace.
Text.LocalizedString: I like the cold wind. It feels good against my face after a whole day in front of the hot furnace.

Text.SourceString: I'm bringing some fish to the potluck. Not really into vegetables.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm bringing some fish to the potluck. Not really into vegetables.

Text.SourceString: Umm… I meant for the Cherry Blossom Festival.
Text.LocalizedString: Umm… I meant for the Cherry Blossom Festival.

Text.SourceString: You can actually turn canola into oil with an oil maker.//Um, I don’t think you can buy oil makers, but once you have the blueprint, making one is pretty simple.
Text.LocalizedString: You can actually turn canola into oil with an oil maker.//Um, I don’t think you can buy oil makers, but once you have the blueprint, making one is pretty simple.

Text.SourceString: For some reason, mosquitos don’t bite me. Isn’t that weird?
Text.LocalizedString: For some reason, mosquitos don’t bite me. Isn’t that weird?

Text.SourceString: I brought some edamame for <NPCName>Valentina</> yesterday. I keep forgetting she hates it.//I hope she doesn’t hate me now.
Text.LocalizedString: I brought some edamame for <NPCName>Valentina</> yesterday. I keep forgetting she hates it.//I hope she doesn’t hate me now.

Text.SourceString: I would probably fish if I didn’t have to keep my parents’ shop open.
Text.LocalizedString: I would probably fish if I didn’t have to keep my parents’ shop open.

Text.SourceString: That would be a very different life for me.
Text.LocalizedString: That would be a very different life for me.

Text.SourceString: Eating something cold like cold fish or ice cream would be good right about now.
Text.LocalizedString: Eating something cold like cold fish or ice cream would be good right about now.

Text.SourceString: The majority of the trash here drifted in from the sea. Can you imagine what it’s like where this trash came from?
Text.LocalizedString: The majority of the trash here drifted in from the sea. Can you imagine what it’s like where this trash came from?

Text.SourceString: I, um, need to go to the clinic this week… For, um, personal matters.
Text.LocalizedString: I, um, need to go to the clinic this week… For, um, personal matters.

Text.SourceString: Heh heh… What? You look happy today.//It kind of makes me happy to see.
Text.LocalizedString: Heh heh… What? You look happy today.//It kind of makes me happy to see.

Text.SourceString: Today is the last day of Summer, yet the heat doesn’t want to let up.
Text.LocalizedString: Today is the last day of Summer, yet the heat doesn’t want to let up.

Text.SourceString: I’m not doing anything special today. It’s just another Thursday for me. What about you?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not doing anything special today. It’s just another Thursday for me. What about you?

Text.SourceString: I’m not doing anything special today. It’s just another Thursday for me. What about you?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not doing anything special today. It’s just another Thursday for me. What about you?

Text.SourceString: I’m not doing anything special today. It’s just another Thursday for me. What about you?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not doing anything special today. It’s just another Thursday for me. What about you?

Text.SourceString: I like the cold wind. It feels good against my face after a whole day in front of the hot furnace.
Text.LocalizedString: I like the cold wind. It feels good against my face after a whole day in front of the hot furnace.

Text.SourceString: I hope Stephen’s claw grows back real soon so he can go back to exploring the sea.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope Stephen’s claw grows back real soon so he can go back to exploring the sea.

Text.SourceString: Oh! Umm, Stephen is <NPCName>Macy’s</> adopted lobster.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! Umm, Stephen is <NPCName>Macy’s</> adopted lobster.

Text.SourceString: My parents aren’t originally from Coral Island.// They sort of, um, arrived here from Dulca Island when they were young. They came with two of my uncles.
Text.LocalizedString: My parents aren’t originally from Coral Island.// They sort of, um, arrived here from Dulca Island when they were young. They came with two of my uncles.

Text.SourceString: Dulca Island is, like, really far from here.//<portrait=normal>When we were kids, our parents would sometimes take <NPCName>Pablo</> and me there to visit our grandparents. But, um, not too often.
Text.LocalizedString: Dulca Island is, like, really far from here.//<portrait=normal>When we were kids, our parents would sometimes take <NPCName>Pablo</> and me there to visit our grandparents. But, um, not too often.

Text.SourceString: Winter is a great time to upgrade your tools. You'd be ready for a busy Spring then.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter is a great time to upgrade your tools. You'd be ready for a busy Spring then.

Text.SourceString: I like the cold wind. It feels nice against my face after spending all day near the hot furnace.
Text.LocalizedString: I like the cold wind. It feels nice against my face after spending all day near the hot furnace.

Text.SourceString: Hot-air balloon rides kind of scare me. But, um, I'd like to try someday.
Text.LocalizedString: Hot-air balloon rides kind of scare me. But, um, I'd like to try someday.

Text.SourceString: And…my stomach hurts thinking about it.
Text.LocalizedString: And…my stomach hurts thinking about it.

Text.SourceString: I’m kind of nervous about <NPCName>Bree</>'s dinner party tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m kind of nervous about <NPCName>Bree</>'s dinner party tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: I’m afraid I might say the wrong thing and ruin people’s dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m afraid I might say the wrong thing and ruin people’s dinner.

Text.SourceString: I hope it starts raining soon.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it starts raining soon.

Text.SourceString: The walking path could do with a good rinse.
Text.LocalizedString: The walking path could do with a good rinse.

Text.SourceString: The rain makes for some relaxing white noise in the background, don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: The rain makes for some relaxing white noise in the background, don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: *yawns*
Text.LocalizedString: *yawns*

Text.SourceString: Um, I feel a bit weird talking here.
Text.LocalizedString: Um, I feel a bit weird talking here.

Text.SourceString: The rain makes for some relaxing white noise in the background, don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: The rain makes for some relaxing white noise in the background, don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: *yawns*
Text.LocalizedString: *yawns*

Text.SourceString: Oh no! I need to dry off my boots. Mud everywhere!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no! I need to dry off my boots. Mud everywhere!

Text.SourceString: Oh well.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh well.

Text.SourceString: A storm like this blew our roof off one time.//<portrait=sad>We had to relocate for a few days while it was being fixed.
Text.LocalizedString: A storm like this blew our roof off one time.//<portrait=sad>We had to relocate for a few days while it was being fixed.

Text.SourceString: I’m sure your cabin will be fine, though. Don’t worry.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m sure your cabin will be fine, though. Don’t worry.

Text.SourceString: It’s, um, storming outside.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s, um, storming outside.

Text.SourceString: It’s, um, storming outside.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s, um, storming outside.

Text.SourceString: The rain is relaxing, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: The rain is relaxing, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: Walking's a bit tough when it's raining, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Walking's a bit tough when it's raining, though.

Text.SourceString: I have this habit of spending too much on stuff I don’t need at the fair.
Text.LocalizedString: I have this habit of spending too much on stuff I don’t need at the fair.

Text.SourceString: They make a stop here every year before going down south.
Text.LocalizedString: They make a stop here every year before going down south.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ben</>'s part of it. But I think he stays here, in Coral Island.//<portrait=normal>Only travels once a year.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ben</>'s part of it. But I think he stays here, in Coral Island.//<portrait=normal>Only travels once a year.

Text.SourceString: The snow helps me build up a resistance to cold weather.
Text.LocalizedString: The snow helps me build up a resistance to cold weather.

Text.SourceString: You can find all sorts of shiny things in the cavern.//If you dig deep enough, there are plenty of diamonds and stuff. Just watch out for those scary bugs, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: You can find all sorts of shiny things in the cavern.//If you dig deep enough, there are plenty of diamonds and stuff. Just watch out for those scary bugs, okay?

Text.SourceString: Calling it a day and going to rest. I’ll continue tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Calling it a day and going to rest. I’ll continue tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Don’t slip on the way home.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t slip on the way home.

Text.SourceString: I’m just cleaning up a bit of moss on the stones.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m just cleaning up a bit of moss on the stones.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I come here to read a book. It’s nice and quiet.//<portrait=normal>What are you, um, doing here?
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I come here to read a book. It’s nice and quiet.//<portrait=normal>What are you, um, doing here?

Text.SourceString: Some of the books here are very odd.//<portrait=annoyed>I think I read something about a flying dog one time.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of the books here are very odd.//<portrait=annoyed>I think I read something about a flying dog one time.

Text.SourceString: It was probably <NPCName>Alice</>'s.//<portrait=normal>That girl is out of this world with her theories.
Text.LocalizedString: It was probably <NPCName>Alice</>'s.//<portrait=normal>That girl is out of this world with her theories.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Taco</> lived here for a few weeks.//Then <NPCName>Suki</> took him over to <NPCName>Luke</>'s for a playdate, and the pup, um, didn’t want to come back.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Taco</> lived here for a few weeks.//Then <NPCName>Suki</> took him over to <NPCName>Luke</>'s for a playdate, and the pup, um, didn’t want to come back.

Text.SourceString: So <NPCName>Taco</> lives there now.
Text.LocalizedString: So <NPCName>Taco</> lives there now.

Text.SourceString: I don’t take orders outside of the shop.//If you want to get your tools upgraded, come by the shop tomorrow, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t take orders outside of the shop.//If you want to get your tools upgraded, come by the shop tomorrow, okay?

Text.SourceString: You can always tell when my brother walks into a room.//Any room, really… Conversations seem to get livelier, don’t they?
Text.LocalizedString: You can always tell when my brother walks into a room.//Any room, really… Conversations seem to get livelier, don’t they?

Text.SourceString: When <NPCName>Pablo</> tells jokes, my parents laugh harder, you know… Simple stuff like that.//<portrait=concerned>People don’t notice, but I do.
Text.LocalizedString: When <NPCName>Pablo</> tells jokes, my parents laugh harder, you know… Simple stuff like that.//<portrait=concerned>People don’t notice, but I do.

Text.SourceString: Upgrading a tool, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Upgrading a tool, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Getting the right weapon can really help with slaying certain monsters.
Text.LocalizedString: Getting the right weapon can really help with slaying certain monsters.

Text.SourceString: In my downtime, I sometimes mine for ore in the cavern to make weapons.//You can always count on our store if you need ore right away.
Text.LocalizedString: In my downtime, I sometimes mine for ore in the cavern to make weapons.//You can always count on our store if you need ore right away.

Text.SourceString: I need to go back to work.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to go back to work.

Text.SourceString: Oh, umm… I came here for some tacos.//I’m not in the mood to cook anything.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, umm… I came here for some tacos.//I’m not in the mood to cook anything.

Text.SourceString: I’m going back to work after this.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going back to work after this.

Text.SourceString: It feels good to be outside every once in a while.//<portrait=normal>The shop is way too hot sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels good to be outside every once in a while.//<portrait=normal>The shop is way too hot sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I don’t usually come here, but it’s <NPCName>Pablo</>'s birthday today, so I just came out for a celebratory meal.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t usually come here, but it’s <NPCName>Pablo</>'s birthday today, so I just came out for a celebratory meal.

Text.SourceString: I never noticed how loud it is in here. Wow!
Text.LocalizedString: I never noticed how loud it is in here. Wow!

Text.SourceString: I should go home soon. I feel exhausted.
Text.LocalizedString: I should go home soon. I feel exhausted.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Pablo</> and I went to the inn and had a quick dinner with our niece, <NPCName>Valentina</>, to celebrate her birthday last week.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Pablo</> and I went to the inn and had a quick dinner with our niece, <NPCName>Valentina</>, to celebrate her birthday last week.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Pablo</> gave her a geode because he thought she’d enjoy finding treasures, but I guess not…
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Pablo</> gave her a geode because he thought she’d enjoy finding treasures, but I guess not…

Text.SourceString: Errr… It’s nice to have you around.
Text.LocalizedString: Errr… It’s nice to have you around.

Text.SourceString: Thanks for always checking up on me.//You’re a good friend.
Text.LocalizedString: Thanks for always checking up on me.//You’re a good friend.

Text.SourceString: I carry around an iron morning star with me.//You never really know what you’ll run into on this island.
Text.LocalizedString: I carry around an iron morning star with me.//You never really know what you’ll run into on this island.

Text.SourceString: It’s my own handmade weapon, of course. It does great damage, and I’m quite proud.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s my own handmade weapon, of course. It does great damage, and I’m quite proud.

Text.SourceString: I know I can be a bit dull sometimes… Or I’m just not very good at this friend thing.//<portrait=normal>But please know I’m trying.
Text.LocalizedString: I know I can be a bit dull sometimes… Or I’m just not very good at this friend thing.//<portrait=normal>But please know I’m trying.

Text.SourceString: I might get new swimming trunks from <NPCName>Antonio’s</> shop.//<portrait=annoyed>Things are just so expensive there, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I might get new swimming trunks from <NPCName>Antonio’s</> shop.//<portrait=annoyed>Things are just so expensive there, though.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kira</> has a great selection of weapons and armor.//Have you checked them out yet?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kira</> has a great selection of weapons and armor.//Have you checked them out yet?

Text.SourceString: She doesn’t show them around, but I think she’ll give you some pieces if you help her with the monsters.
Text.LocalizedString: She doesn’t show them around, but I think she’ll give you some pieces if you help her with the monsters.

Text.SourceString: I’ve only seen a blue goblin katana twice. I’m pretty sure <NPCName>Kira</> has one, and we sold one a long time ago.//<portrait=happy>That was pretty cool.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve only seen a blue goblin katana twice. I’m pretty sure <NPCName>Kira</> has one, and we sold one a long time ago.//<portrait=happy>That was pretty cool.

Text.SourceString: I was going to keep the katana, but the offer was too good. Oh well.
Text.LocalizedString: I was going to keep the katana, but the offer was too good. Oh well.

Text.SourceString: If I make the Ironeye Hammer without pure tevandium, I’m not sure what will happen.//Probably nothing.
Text.LocalizedString: If I make the Ironeye Hammer without pure tevandium, I’m not sure what will happen.//Probably nothing.

Text.SourceString: But then again, maybe something. Shouldn’t I take that chance?
Text.LocalizedString: But then again, maybe something. Shouldn’t I take that chance?

Text.SourceString: If I can’t forge the Ironeye Hammer, I suppose I could sell the tevandium. Recoup some of my losses…
Text.LocalizedString: If I can’t forge the Ironeye Hammer, I suppose I could sell the tevandium. Recoup some of my losses…

Text.SourceString: The Ironeye Hammer is supposed to talk to you while it works.//Should I give it a mouth? Does it matter?
Text.LocalizedString: The Ironeye Hammer is supposed to talk to you while it works.//Should I give it a mouth? Does it matter?

Text.SourceString: Every blacksmith worth his iron knows how to make the Ironeye Hammer. The plans are passed down from master to apprentice.//The only hard part has been obtaining the tevandium.
Text.LocalizedString: Every blacksmith worth his iron knows how to make the Ironeye Hammer. The plans are passed down from master to apprentice.//The only hard part has been obtaining the tevandium.

Text.SourceString: Until now, that is.
Text.LocalizedString: Until now, that is.

Text.SourceString: Wear your armor, <PlayerName>$player</>. It really helps with combat.
Text.LocalizedString: Wear your armor, <PlayerName>$player</>. It really helps with combat.

Text.SourceString: Oh… Umm… Yeah, of course I care.//You’re my friend.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh… Umm… Yeah, of course I care.//You’re my friend.

Text.SourceString: Wear your armor, <PlayerName>$player</>. It really helps with combat.
Text.LocalizedString: Wear your armor, <PlayerName>$player</>. It really helps with combat.

Text.SourceString: Oh… Umm… Yeah, of course I care.//I care about you…a lot.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh… Umm… Yeah, of course I care.//I care about you…a lot.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I can, um, come with you when you go to the cavern sometime.//<portrait=blushing>I can protect you, and you can mine in peace.//That way, you won’t get injured.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I can, um, come with you when you go to the cavern sometime.//<portrait=blushing>I can protect you, and you can mine in peace.//That way, you won’t get injured.

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry about me. I’ll be fine.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry about me. I’ll be fine.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kira</> is cool. I grew up wanting to be like her, fighting monsters, living in the middle of nowhere, and all that…//But that’s not the life for me. No, I belong here, in my parents’ shack.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kira</> is cool. I grew up wanting to be like her, fighting monsters, living in the middle of nowhere, and all that…//But that’s not the life for me. No, I belong here, in my parents’ shack.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Yuri</> reminds me of <NPCName>Kira</> a little.//She’s brave and saves a lot of lives, I bet.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Yuri</> reminds me of <NPCName>Kira</> a little.//She’s brave and saves a lot of lives, I bet.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard to sleep when <NPCName>Emma</> has private events at her food truck.//They usually last past midnight, and the music is a bit loud.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard to sleep when <NPCName>Emma</> has private events at her food truck.//They usually last past midnight, and the music is a bit loud.

Text.SourceString: I’m happy she gets extra income, but I secretly hope she doesn’t do it too often.//Does that make me a bad friend?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m happy she gets extra income, but I secretly hope she doesn’t do it too often.//Does that make me a bad friend?

Text.SourceString: Um, are you okay? I'm not, um, making you uncomfortable, am I?//What is it?
Text.LocalizedString: Um, are you okay? I'm not, um, making you uncomfortable, am I?//What is it?

Text.SourceString: Umm… I could come over and cook for you. That might help a little.//<portrait=blushing>Or if you need anything else…I’d be up for that too.
Text.LocalizedString: Umm… I could come over and cook for you. That might help a little.//<portrait=blushing>Or if you need anything else…I’d be up for that too.

Text.SourceString: I feel, um, kinda bad saying no to people, <PlayerName>$player</>. I don’t know… I feel impolite, I guess.//I’ve heard you turn down a lot of things.//Could you, um, teach me your ways?
Text.LocalizedString: I feel, um, kinda bad saying no to people, <PlayerName>$player</>. I don’t know… I feel impolite, I guess.//I’ve heard you turn down a lot of things.//Could you, um, teach me your ways?

Text.SourceString: Oh, uh… I didn’t mean it that way.//<portrait=blushing>I meant… You’re an honest person, and I can learn a lot from you.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, uh… I didn’t mean it that way.//<portrait=blushing>I meant… You’re an honest person, and I can learn a lot from you.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know how to say this… I’ve never met anyone like you.//You’re…different.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know how to say this… I’ve never met anyone like you.//You’re…different.

Text.SourceString: You’re kinda funny… Always with the smart comebacks.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re kinda funny… Always with the smart comebacks.

Text.SourceString: I should just fish and make sashimi for dinner tonight.//<portrait=normal>I’m starving! I could eat a giant bowl of it.
Text.LocalizedString: I should just fish and make sashimi for dinner tonight.//<portrait=normal>I’m starving! I could eat a giant bowl of it.

Text.SourceString: We got plenty of salmon the other day!//I might make sashimi for dinner tonight. Yummy!
Text.LocalizedString: We got plenty of salmon the other day!//I might make sashimi for dinner tonight. Yummy!

Text.SourceString: I think I overworked myself yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I overworked myself yesterday.

Text.SourceString: I hope you know I really like hanging out with you. I feel like I can finally be myself around you.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you know I really like hanging out with you. I feel like I can finally be myself around you.

Text.SourceString: If there’s something I don’t do enough, just let me know, okay?//<portrait=confused>I’m too scared to bother you sometimes, so I like to keep my distance.
Text.LocalizedString: If there’s something I don’t do enough, just let me know, okay?//<portrait=confused>I’m too scared to bother you sometimes, so I like to keep my distance.

Text.SourceString: I want to make sure you get what you need.//<portrait=normal>It’s very important to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I want to make sure you get what you need.//<portrait=normal>It’s very important to me.

Text.SourceString: I made a mace for the shop last week. It’s one of my best ones so far. Want to give it a swing?
Text.LocalizedString: I made a mace for the shop last week. It’s one of my best ones so far. Want to give it a swing?

Text.SourceString: I guess you could raise a bunch of kids in a big place like yours.//Well, if you’re into that type of thing, that is.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess you could raise a bunch of kids in a big place like yours.//Well, if you’re into that type of thing, that is.

Text.SourceString: Family, settling down. You know the drill.//<portrait=normal>My brother talks about having a big family all the time. For me, I’m happy by myself, but who knows.
Text.LocalizedString: Family, settling down. You know the drill.//<portrait=normal>My brother talks about having a big family all the time. For me, I’m happy by myself, but who knows.

Text.SourceString: Can’t bake cookies. My oven is broken, and I’m too lazy to fix it.
Text.LocalizedString: Can’t bake cookies. My oven is broken, and I’m too lazy to fix it.

Text.SourceString: That sounds great. Umm…
Text.LocalizedString: That sounds great. Umm…

Special.SourceString: You can bake cookies at my house. We could watch TV and eat them together.
Special.LocalizedString: You can bake cookies at my house. We could watch TV and eat them together.

Text.SourceString: Ha ha. Very funny.
Text.LocalizedString: Ha ha. Very funny.

Special.SourceString: Aren’t you like a handyman or something?
Special.LocalizedString: Aren’t you like a handyman or something?

Text.SourceString: Yeah. No big deal.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah. No big deal.

Special.SourceString: I’d let you use my oven if I had one. Sorry!
Special.LocalizedString: I’d let you use my oven if I had one. Sorry!

Text.SourceString: Yeah, I know. Oh well. No big deal.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, I know. Oh well. No big deal.

Special.SourceString: Oh no! Hopefully, it’ll get fixed soon.
Special.LocalizedString: Oh no! Hopefully, it’ll get fixed soon.

Text.SourceString: Did you hear that?
Text.LocalizedString: Did you hear that?

Text.SourceString: No, I’m not teasing you. But it was probably just the wind or something.
Text.LocalizedString: No, I’m not teasing you. But it was probably just the wind or something.

Text.SourceString: Growing up with someone like <NPCName>Pablo</>, I started noticing things that shouldn’t be a big deal.//<portrait=concerned>Can’t help it… Just an insecurity of mine after being in his shadow my whole life.
Text.LocalizedString: Growing up with someone like <NPCName>Pablo</>, I started noticing things that shouldn’t be a big deal.//<portrait=concerned>Can’t help it… Just an insecurity of mine after being in his shadow my whole life.

Text.SourceString: Probably for the best, though. Too much attention wrecks me, anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: Probably for the best, though. Too much attention wrecks me, anyway.

Text.SourceString: The lake must be relaxing on a Spring day like this.//I might check it out later.//<portrait=annoyed>No, no. Maybe tomorrow. Yeah!
Text.LocalizedString: The lake must be relaxing on a Spring day like this.//I might check it out later.//<portrait=annoyed>No, no. Maybe tomorrow. Yeah!

Text.SourceString: We’re welcoming Spring soon.//I think I’ll bring some mushrooms to the potluck. We have plenty in the chest.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re welcoming Spring soon.//I think I’ll bring some mushrooms to the potluck. We have plenty in the chest.

Text.SourceString: The hot spring is too hot for me in Summer. I avoid it. But now that it's nice and cold...
Text.LocalizedString: The hot spring is too hot for me in Summer. I avoid it. But now that it's nice and cold...

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry, I wash this towel every day. In this heat, you gotta.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry, I wash this towel every day. In this heat, you gotta.

Text.SourceString: I saw <NpcName>Lily</> near the lake last week.//I see her there often, and usually she’s all alone. I hope things are okay with her.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NpcName>Lily</> near the lake last week.//I see her there often, and usually she’s all alone. I hope things are okay with her.

Text.SourceString: My cousin, <NpcName>Antonio</>, hooked me up with this jacket.//<portrait=normal>It’s hard to do my job in it, but the fabric feels really nice.
Text.LocalizedString: My cousin, <NpcName>Antonio</>, hooked me up with this jacket.//<portrait=normal>It’s hard to do my job in it, but the fabric feels really nice.

Text.SourceString: It feels weird, putting on a dress shirt, a jacket, and the whole shebang, but <NpcName>Antonio</> said it’s the style nowadays, so…//<portrait=happy>Mom said it makes me look fancy.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels weird, putting on a dress shirt, a jacket, and the whole shebang, but <NpcName>Antonio</> said it’s the style nowadays, so…//<portrait=happy>Mom said it makes me look fancy.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Valentina</> made me this beanie.//Can you see the tiny little bear on it? I love it.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Valentina</> made me this beanie.//Can you see the tiny little bear on it? I love it.

Text.SourceString: I like this jacket. It’s nice and warm.
